parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption and Engine Problems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, premature wear, and potentially cause accidents due to loss of power or stalling. It can also result in costly repairs and leave drivers stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic. It can also lead to a loss of control and increase the risk of collisions.

The automatic disengagement of the steering wheel paddle shifters can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, especially in inclement weather or steep downgrades, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The paddle shifters turn off automatically
the vehicle shifts into higher gears
causing acceleration when going downhill or slowing in slippery conditions
the accelerator pedal becomes very touchy in Sport mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver, especially in situations where engine braking is necessary.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Failure and Inadequate Crash Protection
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belts to restrain occupants during a crash can lead to severe injuries or fatalities, and the malfunction of the Low-Speed Collision Avoidance and Collision Warning with Full Auto Brake Systems can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Seat belts fail to restrain occupants
vehicles are deemed a total loss.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Crash Protection and Safety Features Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of safety features, such as the Low-Speed Collision Avoidance and Collision Warning with Full Auto Brake Systems, can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: vehicles are deemed a total loss.
